  "prompt": "How do you jump to a certain page of a PDF file on the iPhone?",
  "response": "To jump to a certain page of a PDF file on your iPhone, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the PDF**: Use a PDF viewer app like Apple's Books, Files, or any third-party app (like Adobe Acrobat Reader).\n\n2. **Access the Page Navigation**:\n   - In Apps like **Books** or **Files**:\n     - Tap on the screen to bring up the navigation controls.\n     - Look for a page indicator that shows the current page number and the total number of pages (e.g., \"1/20\").\n     - Tap on that indicator, and a page navigation dialog should appear.\n   - In **Adobe Acrobat Reader** or similar apps:\n     - Tap on the page indicator or search for a \"Go to Page\" option usually found in the menu.\n\n3. **Enter the Page Number**: Once you access the page navigation dialog, type in the page number you want to jump to.\n\n4. **Go to the Page**: After entering the page number, hit the \"Enter\" or \"Go\" button, and the app should take you directly to the specified page.\n\nThis method may vary slightly based on the app you are using, but most PDF readers have a similar way to navigate pages.",
